-- Capital One Hires Goldman’s Steven Tulip to Head Capital Markets
-- B y   D a k i n   C a m p b e l l
-- 2013-08-14T19:20:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-14/capital-one-hires-goldman-s-steven-tulip-to-head-capital-markets.html
Capital One Financial Corp. (COF) , the
lender that gets more than half its revenue from credit cards,
hired former Goldman Sachs Group Inc. banker Steven Tulip to
head its capital-markets business.  Tulip, most recently a managing director at Goldman Sachs,
will expand Capital One’s broker-dealer and offer more products
such as loan syndications and interest-rate and commodities
derivatives, according to a statement today from the McLean,
Virginia-based lender. He’ll report to Michael Slocum,
commercial banking group president.  Tulip also spent 20 years at  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) , where he
was a managing director in charge of health care and industrials
leveraged finance, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
